<p><strong>Re: Request for Itemized Bill</strong><br>
Patient: {{senderName}}<br>
{{#if accountNumber}}Account Number: {{accountNumber}}<br>{{/if}}
Date(s) of Service: {{formatDate dateOfService}}<br>
Amount Billed: {{formatCurrency billAmount}}</p>

<p>Dear Billing Department:</p>

<p>I am writing to request a complete itemized bill for the medical services referenced above. I received a summary statement showing a total balance of {{formatCurrency billAmount}}, but I have not received a detailed breakdown of individual charges.</p>

<p>I am requesting an itemized statement that includes:</p>

<ol>
<li>Each individual charge listed separately with its corresponding CPT/HCPCS billing code</li>
<li>A description of each service, procedure, or supply</li>
<li>The date each service was provided</li>
<li>The name and credentials of the provider who rendered each service</li>
<li>The quantity and unit price for each item</li>
<li>Any adjustments, discounts, or insurance payments applied</li>
</ol>

<p>This request is made pursuant to my rights as a patient to receive a detailed accounting of charges for services rendered. Federal regulations and most state consumer protection laws require healthcare providers to furnish itemized bills upon patient request.</p>

<p>Please provide this itemized statement within 30 days of receipt of this letter. I am sending this letter via certified mail to document my request and establish a record of the date it was received.</p>

<p>Please do not take any collection action, including reporting to credit bureaus, while this request is being processed. I am not disputing the debt at this time; I am exercising my right to receive a complete accounting of charges before making payment arrangements.</p>

<p>Please send the itemized statement to the address listed above. If you have any questions, you may contact me at the address above.</p>

<p>Sincerely,</p>

<br><br>

<p>{{senderName}}</p>

<br>

<p style="font-size: 10pt; font-style: italic;">Sent via USPS Certified Mail, Return Receipt Requested</p>

